arch:property.oc:show_val: Phase X: Site abandonment after major collapse dating to the Byzantine period from the CE 4th to 5th c. New drainage systems are installed including that associated with the newly built west precinct wall.
0.52 m north south -by- 1.25 m east west.

Locus 74 is the blockage between the second and third columns from the west of the colonnade, located to the west of the small cistern. The blockage consists of hewn and dressed sandstone ashlars, some in reuse, and snecking stones. The ashlars are dry-laid in two rows and three courses. This blockage is phased to Stage 4, the post-363 repairs and reworking of the Complex, including this filling in of the gaps between the columns in the colonnade.
Post-363 reworking of the Complex, including blockage of doorways and the covering of the ornamental pool.
Intercolumnar blockage just west of the small cistern
